                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 590.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Valera</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain at Washington</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-10-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 10, 1885</date>. (Received October
                        12.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of His Majesty
                    the King of Spain, has the honor, referring to his note of the 6th instant, to
                    send to the honorable Thomas F. Bayard, Secretary of State of the United States,
                    the inclosed check for $7,987.80, being the amount of the claims presented by
                    the United States Government to that of His Majesty the King in behalf of
                    several American exporters of cattle to the island of Cuba via the port of Key
                    West.</p>
                <p>The accompanying table shows the names of the vessels, the number of head of
                    cattle exported, the duties collected by the consulate of Spain, and the amount
                    refunded to each exporter.</p>
                <p>The undersigned minister begs the honorable Secretary of State to be pleased to
                    acknowledge the receipt of this amount, and he gladly avails himself,
                    &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JUAN VALERA.</signed>
                </closer>
